channel.title: Hey, guys...I have a problem with Java
channel.description:
Some of you may remember me from ZytheScape, my name is Sk1ll3r F2p ;D. Almost every time I try to get into a server, a client error occurs in my java.exe..[i]something like this:[/i]
You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
[i][u][b]Or:[/b][/u][/i]
Oh dear, you do not have JDK 6. Please download it from (insert link here).
I have tried to figure out which one to download, and none of them work so far. If someone could give me the direct link..that would be awesome! Thanks, plz reply if possible!

item.title: Hey, guys...I have a problem with Java
item.dc:creator: @bigh51 bigh51
item.description:
@bigh51 wrote:

That’s not java.exe, that’s compiler.bat which is a batch file that calls the javac.exe and run.bat or server.bat calls the file java.exe. The problem is, you don’t have your path’s set properly. Set them properly.
